I am the MT for my guild which is able to kill Lord Bob and think able to kill Velk too but haven’t tried and working towards Vindi. I have been using Ornate General Sword and Frosty. They allowed me to hold aggro pretty well.<br>
<br>
However, here comes my question that I gave up my Frosty for LSoF when one dropped last nite in a UP raid. <br>
My gut feeling told me that Frosty is a better taunt weapon than LSoF.  However, when I looked at the stat and the ratio of LSoF, I cannot resist having my hand on it and based on my guild’s informal rule, I passed down my frosty to the next best warriors. <br>
<br>
So now, my weapons are Ornated General  Sword and LSoF. <br>
<br>
